article.headline: Winthrop 90, Ferrum 62
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- James Shuler led four Winthrop players in double figures as Winthrop beat Ferrum 90-62 Sunday afternoon in the Eagles' final game before Big South Conference play begins. Shuler scored 15, followed by Phillip Williams who scored a career-high 13 and grabbed a team-high seven rebounds. Craig Bradshaw added 12 and Billy Houston had 10 for Winthrop (9-4). Ferrum's (3-7) Kenny Johnson had 27 points, including four 3-pointers, to lead all scorers. Johnson also led his team with five assists and he and Nigel Kelly grabbed seven rebounds a piece. Winthrop shot 58 percent to Ferrum's 40 percent and led 46-35 at the half.
